        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 2:53PM MDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 252 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 9 miles north of Hope to 11
miles west of Seven Rivers Airport to 15 miles east of Lincoln
National Forest. Movement was east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Artesia, Hope, Brantley Lake State Park, Seven Rivers Airport,
Lincoln National Forest, Artesia Municipal Airport, Atoka, Dayton,
and Lakewood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
